SIMPLE: initiation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Initiation
<hw>In*i`ti*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>initiatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>initiation</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of initiating, or the process of being
initiated or introduced; <as>as, <ex>initiation</ex> into a society,
into business, literature, etc.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>initiation</xex> of courses of events.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The form or ceremony by which a person is introduced
into any society; mode of entrance into an organized body; especially,
the rite of admission into a secret society or order.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Silence is the first thing that is taught us at our
<qex>initiation</qex> into sacred mysteries.</q>
<rj><qau>Broome.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Initiative</ent>⟦br⟧
